Police have launched a manhunt for a group of persons allegedly involved in the killing of Ailwei Samuel Tshifhango (64) at his home in Louis Trichardt on Tuesday evening.
Provincial Police Spokesperson Moatshe Ngoepe indicated that the 64-year-old taxi owner was allegedly attacked by a group of suspects as he was about to enter his home between 17:00 and 18:00.
He was shot and the suspects reportedly fled the scene in a black Volkswagen Jetta and a white Volkswagen Polo with unknown registration numbers, according to Ngoepe.
He remarked that Police and emergency personnel speedily reached the scene and immediately transported the victim to hospital where he was certified dead on arrival.
Ngoepe said that the motive behind the incident was not clear yet but that taxi violence cannot be ruled out.
Anyone with information can contact investigating officer Nyelisani Mabatha on 082 565 8171 or report to the nearest Police station.
